  RFC9040 [label="RFC9040
TCP Control Block Interdependence
2021", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC9040.html", target="_top", tooltip="This memo provides guidance to TCP implementers that is intended to help improve connection convergence to steady-state operation without affecting interoperability.  It updates and replaces RFC 2140's description of sharing TCP state, as typically represented in TCP Control Blocks, among similar concurrent or consecutive connections."];
